"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-arkansas-hogs-news-razorback-sets-new-olympic-record-strikes-gold-in-paris\", \"text\": \"In this story:  PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 All you need is one. In field events, all you need is one perfectly executed attempt to carry you  to Olympic Glory. Arkansas alum Roje Stona's throw in the fourth round out of six of 70 meters in the discus final was enough for the contingent of Hogs to pick up their first gold medal of these Olympics.  Truly an underdog story right there\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00ae.Jamaica's\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00af\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b2 Roje Stona in 8th place, throwing a 70m, a personal best, breaking the#OlympicRecord just set by Lithuania's\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b1\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b9 Alekna of 69.97m and getting First Spot where he remained for the\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u008fpic.twitter.com/BTzzhWcZKQ  The throw not only was a personal best for Stona, but broke a 20 -year-old Olympic record set by Virgilijus Alekena in Athens 2004 of 69.89 meters. Prior to that throw, Stona was sitting in eighth place.  Mykolas Alekna, the son of Virgilijus and presumptive gold medal favorite, having smashed the world record earlier this year in Roman, Oklahoma finished in the silver medal for Lithuania position just behind with a throw of 69.97 meters. Matthew Denny of Australia rounded out the podium with a bronze medal throw of 69.31 meters.  This is the fourth medal that the Razorback contingent has picked up on the track at the Paris Olympics. Stona follows in the footsteps ofAmber Anning, Kaylyn BrownandWayne Pinnockbringing back a piece of the Eiffel Tower stateside.  HOGS FEED:  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2\\u00c2All agree: Razorbacks' underrated player on defensive front  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2\\u00c2Hogs' Fouch wanting receivers to understand opportunity  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2\\u00c2Broden possible breakout candidate at WR for Razorbacks  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Subscribe and follow us on\\u00c2YouTube\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Follow allHOGS on\\u00c2X\\u00c2and\\u00c2Facebook  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Covers baseball, football and basketball for Arkansas Razorback on SI since 2023, previously writing for FanSided. Currently a student at the University of Arkansas. He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been repeatedly jaded by the Los Angeles Angels since 2014. Probably silently humming along to whatever the band is playing in the press box. Follow me on X: @dsh12  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"